<p>Our last featured suggestion is one that may be slightly controversial. It is now becoming a common trend for offices to do without reception areas, clearing up valuable space if you do not deal with a lot of clientele coming into your office. If you don&#8217;t have a lot of business coming to your office then consider removing the reception area. You will save money on the expensive rental space and you can use it for other things.</p>
